---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - ChurnPill" description="Learn about ChurnPill's mission to help SaaS founders reduce churn and save revenue with simple, effective solutions.">
  <div class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <svg aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 size-full mask-[radial-gradient(100%_100%_at_top_right,white,transparent)] stroke-gray-200 dark:stroke-white/10">
      <defs>
        <pattern id="about-pattern" width="200" height="200" x="50%" y="-1" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
          <path d="M.5 200V.5H200" fill="none" />
        </pattern>
      </defs>
      <svg x="50%" y="-1" class="overflow-visible fill-gray-50 dark:fill-gray-800/20">
        <path d="M-200 0h201v201h-201Z M600 0h201v201h-201Z M-400 600h201v201h-201Z M200 800h201v201h-201Z" stroke-width="0" />
      </svg>
      <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#about-pattern)" stroke-width="0" />
    </svg>
    
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 lg:py-32">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl dark:text-white" style="font-family: 'Gambarino', serif;">About ChurnPill</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300" style="font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;">Simple churn prevention for serious founders</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-16 prose prose-lg mx-auto dark:prose-invert" style="font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-8">
          ChurnPill was built for SaaS founders who are tired of watching revenue walk out the door. We know the pain of seeing customers cancel, especially when you could have saved them with the right intervention at the right time.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-12" style="font-family: 'Gambarino', serif;">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          To make churn prevention accessible to every SaaS business, regardless of size or technical resources. No complex implementations, no months of setup – just connect Stripe, add our snippet, and start saving revenue in minutes.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-12" style="font-family: 'Gambarino', serif;">Why We Built This</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          After seeing too many good businesses struggle with preventable churn, we realized the existing solutions were either too expensive, too complex, or required engineering resources most teams don't have. ChurnPill bridges that gap with a simple, effective approach that works out of the box.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-12" style="font-family: 'Gambarino', serif;">What Makes Us Different</h2>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Zero setup complexity</strong> – Connect and go live in under 10 minutes</li>
          <li><strong>Stripe-native</strong> – Works seamlessly with your existing billing flow</li>
          <li><strong>Founder-focused</strong> – Built by founders, for founders who need results fast</li>
          <li><strong>Revenue-first approach</strong> – Every feature designed to save you money, not just provide data</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="mt-16 text-center">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
            Ready to stop losing revenue to preventable churn?
          </p>
          <a href="/" class="rounded-md bg-primary-600 px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-primary-500 focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-500 dark:hover:bg-primary-400">
            Get Started Today
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
